    "body": "Problem:\r\nI think most Nvim users only use Lua for configuration and plugins, and a common question is that they are warned by the server about the `vim` global variable.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nAdd a bit code to the LuaLS example in `lsp.txt`",
    "closed_at": "2025-03-16T14:29:09Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'd tend to point users towards using `.luarc.json` files instead\r\n\r\nIf we promote setting these options within `lsp.start`/`config` it has the disadvantage that authors of plugins will likely not add `.luarc.json` files which makes the life worse for contributors who also work on lua projects outside the neovim space. (I'm certainly guilty of that)\r\n",
