        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Btw, I have a question. If both a .luarc.json exists, will lua-language-server just use configuration from that file or will it merge that file with Nvim config?\r\n\r\nThe [old GitHub wiki](https://github.com/LuaLS/lua-language-server/wiki/Configuration-File#the-configuration-file) is more explicit about this than the [new documentation page](https://luals.github.io/wiki/configuration/#configuration-file), but I think things are read in the order (1) command line flag `--configpath`, (2) `.luarc`, and (3) client configuration. I've experimented a bit, and it seems that there's no merging. Whichever configuration is found first is the only one applied.",
            "created_at": "2025-03-06T20:34:18Z",
